      "completed_at": "2026-04-08T05:05:59.541011+00:00",
      "artifacts": {
        "changelog_entry": "[#362] T-IMG-001 imaging types prerequisite impl - replaces the `scieasy_blocks_imaging.types` skeleton contract with concrete `Image`, `Mask`, `Label`, and `Transform` implementations. `Image.Meta` now uses typed `PhysicalQuantity` and `ChannelInfo` metadata with JSON round-trip and worker reconstruction coverage; `Mask` enforces boolean dtype; `Label` validates that at least one of `raster` or `polygons` is present and exposes the expected slots contract; `Transform` validates affine-matrix shapes and typed metadata. Imaging smoke coverage moved from the top-level skeleton placeholder into real package tests, and compatibility assertions in the geometry and axis-split suites were updated so already-landed imaging blocks validate against the new typed metadata contract. (@Codex, 2026-04-08, branch: feat/issue-362/T-IMG-001-imaging-types, session: 20260408-004852-phase-11-imaging-types-implementation-ch)"
      }
    }
